(Motivation) s
5 473 M
(The IETF's "Request for Comments" name reflects a historical process we) s
5 462 M
(don't share.[^h1] We don't request comments\342\\200\\224we record decisions. But the) s
5 451 M
(RFC format is well-understood and serves our needs.) s
5 429 M
(The compromise: RFC format externally, "memo" internally.) s
5 407 M
("I penned a memo on wormholes"     \342\\206\\220 what we say) s
5 396 M
("See RFC-041"                       \342\\206\\220 how we cite) s
5 374 M
([^h1]: Historical: The first RFC \(RFC-1, April 1969\) was literally a) s
5 363 M
(request for comments on host software. The name stuck. Fifty-seven years) s
5 352 M
(later, nobody requests comments\342\\200\\224they publish specifications.) s
5 330 M
